  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Any plans to update the mocha version used by hardhat (when running `hardhat test`)?\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/master/packages/hardhat-core/package.json#L84\r\nThe version used is almost two years old (7.2.0).\r\nI'm asking because of BigInt support which was introduced to mocha with version 8.3.0 about a year ago.\r\nThe latest mocha version is 9.2.1 from four days ago.\r\n\r\nE.g. running the following test with `npx hardhat test` gives an `UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning`.\r\n```javascript\r\nconst { expect } = require(\"chai\");\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"Foo\", function() {\r\n  it(\"should foo\", async function() {\r\n    expect(2n).to.equal(3n):\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith newer mocha versions, it fails properly (raises an error instead of a warning).\r\nAre there any workarounds which wouldn't require changes to hardhat itself?",
